record_data.record_plain_text: FERC GAS TARIFF Volume No. 2 of Honeoye Storage Corporation Filed with The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Communications Concerning This Tariff Should Be Addressed To: Richard A. Norman Vice President and Treasurer Honeoye Storage Corporation c/o Essex Hydro Associates, L.L.C. 55 Union Street, 4th Floor Boston, Massachusetts 02108 Telephone: (617) 367-0032 Fax: (617) 367-3796 TABLE OF CONTENTS Volume No. 2 Rate Schedule Customer Sheet No. T-1 National Fuel Gas 2 Distribution Corporation Rate Schedule T-1 Transportation Contract This agreement is made as of the 15 day of July, 1982 and amended effectiveOctober1, 2014, by and between Honeoye Storage Corporation (Honeoye), a New York Corporation and National Fuel Gas Distribution Corporation (NFGDC), a New York Corporation pursuant to the following recitals and representations. NFGDC and Honeoye shall be collectively referred to as "the Parties." ARTICLE I. SCOPE OF CONTRACT 1. During the period beginning on April 1 and October 31 of each year, NFGDC shall make available on a best efforts basis to Honeoye and Honeoye shall receive at the point of receipt (as defined in Article IV), the Transportation Volume determined in accordance with Article II. The Transportation Volume for any contract year (April 1 of a year to March 31 of the next year) shall not exceed 75,000 MCF. 1A. Commencing with the Contract Year beginning in 2014, Article 1, Section 1 of this agreement shall be fully superseded by this Article 1, Section 1A. During the period beginning on November 1 of each year and ending on March 31 of the next year NFGDC shall make available to Honeoye and Honeoye shall receive at the Point of Receipt (as defined in Article IV), a quantity of gas equal to the Transportation Volume determined in accordance with Article IIand Article XV for the previous Contract Year, adjusted to normalized weather conditions, plus any imbalance quantities determined in accordance with Article VII and Article I, Section 1B. The Transportation Volume for any Contract Year (April 1 of a year to March 31 of the next year) shall not exceed 125,000 Dth. The maximum daily quantity that NFGDC may deliver to Honeoye shall be 7,500 Dth unless alternative arrangements are confirmed by NFGDC and Honeoye. Honeoye shall have the right to refuse to accept daily deliveries on behalf of NFGDC to the extent that Honeoye does not have capacity available to receive and store gas. This right of refusal shall not apply to mutually agreed upon and scheduled baseload monthly deliveries. 1B. During the period November 1, 2014 through March 31, 2015, NFGDC shall make available to Honeoye a quantity of gas sufficient to make Honeoye whole for gas delivered by Honeoye to NFGDC during previous periods under this Agreement. 2. Honeoye shall daily transport and deliver on a firm basis to NFGDC at the Points of Delivery (as defined in Article IV), the gas requirement of NFGDC at the existing Points of Delivery in the Honeoye Field, up to a maximum of125,000Dth per Contract Year. 3. NFGDC shall be solely responsible for making gas available at the Point of Receipt and Honeoye shall not be liable hereunder to NFGDC as a result of NFGDC's inability to make gas available. ARTICLE II. TRANSPORTATION VOLUME The Transportation Volume shall be equal to the total volume of natural gas NFGDC takes from the existing Points of Delivery; provided, however, that Honeoye shall not be required to deliver more than 125,000 Dth per year. ARTICLE III. DISPATCHER'S NOTIFICATION 1. NFGDC shall notify Honeoye of the quantity to be received by Honeoye at the Point of Receipt on any day at least 24 hours prior to the commencement of such day. ARTICLE IV. POINTS OF RECEIPT, INTERCONNECTIONS, AND DELIVERY 1. The Point of Receipt for all natural gas to be made available to Honeoye by NFGDC shall be at the existing interconnection of Tennessee Gas Pipeline Company LLC (TGPC) and Honeoye's facilities, adjacent to TGPC's existing 24" pipeline in Ontario County, New York at TGPC's Main Line Valve 236-1. 2. The Points of Delivery for all natural gas to be transported and delivered by Honeoye to NFGDC shall be at the interconnections of Honeoye's and NFGDC's facilities in the area of the Honeoye Gas Field as specified in Exhibit 1, as may be modified from time to time by mutual agreement of the Parties. ARTICLE V. DELIVERY PRESSURE 1. The quantities of natural gas made available by NFGDC to Honeoye shall be at TGPC's line pressure. 2. The natural gas delivered by Honeoye to NFGDC shall not be less than 100 pounds per square inch gauge. ARTICLE VI. DETERMINATION OF DELIVERIES 1. On any day when NFGDC schedules natural gas for delivery at the Point of Receipt, the amount received by Honeoye on such day at such point will be deemed to be the NFGDC volume scheduled by TGPC for delivery to Honeoye. 2. The volume of natural gas delivered by Honeoye to NFGDC hereunder at the various Points of Delivery shall be the actual metered volumes of gas purchased and consumed by NFGDC's customers served from interconnections between Honeoye and NFGDC identified in Exhibit 1 as points NF1, NF2 and NF7, plus the metered quantity measured at NFGDC's meter station at the interconnection identified in Exhibit 1 as point NF11. Honeoye shall have the same rights as NFGDC's retail customers to test the accuracy of NFGDC's meters and to adjust the quantities delivered for any inaccuracies. ARTICLE VII. CONTROL AND BALANCING OF DELIVERIES 1. It is the intent of NFGDC and Honeoye that the quantity of gas delivered by NFGDC to Honeoye during the November 1 to March 31 period will be equal to the Transportation Volume for the previous Contract Year, adjusted to normalized weather conditions. As a consequence, Honeoye and NFGDC recognize that the Transportation Volume in any Contract Year may be greater or less than the corresponding amounts delivered to Honeoye by NFGDC. NFGDC and Honeoye agree that any imbalances between the amounts received by Honeoye from NFGDC and the Transportation Volume will be reconciled in kind in the next Contract Year. To the extent that this agreement terminates, the Parties' obligation to reconcile and make each other whole for such imbalances shall survive such termination and shall be reconciled and resolved during the first year after this agreement terminates. ARTICLE VIII - TERM 1. This agreement shall become effective on the date hereof. This agreement shall continue in force and effect for a primary term ending on March 31, 2023 and shall continue in effect until terminated by NFGDC or Honeoye upon 12 months prior written notice to the other specifying the termination date at the end of or after such initial termination date hereinabove referred to. ARTICLE IX - CONTRACT YEAR 1. Except for the first Contract Year the Contract Year shall begin on April 1 of each year and end on March 31 of each succeeding year. The first Contract Year shall begin on October 1, 2014. ARTICLE X - NOTICES 1. All notices or other written communications provided for or permitted hereunder shall be in writing and shall be deemed to have been duly given when delivered in hand to such party or when mailed by certified or registered mail, postage prepaid, addressed: If to Honeoye: Honeoye Storage Corporation c/o Essex Hydro Associates, L.L.C. 55 Union Street, 4th Floor Boston, Massachusetts 02108 Attn: Honeoye Administrator If to NFGDC: National Fuel Gas Distribution Corporation 6363 Main Street Williamsville, New York 14221-6887 Attn: Gas Supply Administration Department ARTICLE XI. TRANSFER AND ASSIGNMENT OF ALL CONTRACTS 1. Any company which shall succeed by purchase, merger or consolidation to the properties, substantially as an entirety, of either Honeoye or NFGDC, as the case may be, shall be entitled to the rights and shall be subject to the obligations of its predecessor in title under this agreement. Any party may, without relieving itself of its obligations under this agreement, assign any of its rights hereunder to a company with which it is affiliated, but otherwise no assignment of this contract or of any of the rights or obligations thereunder shall be made unless there first shall have been obtained the written consent thereto of NFGDC in the event of an assignment by Honeoye, or the written consent thereto of Honeoye in the event of an assignment by NFGDC. It is agreed, however, that the restrictions on assignment contained in this Article shall not in any way prevent either party to this contract from pledging or mortgaging its rights thereunder as security for its indebtedness. ARTICLE XII. LAW OF CONTRACT 1. The interpretation and performance of this contract shall be in accordance with and controlled by the laws of the State of New York, which shall control regardless of whether any principles of law or equity would result in the application of another jurisdiction's law. ARTICLE XIII. REGULATORY APPROVALS This agreement shall become effective upon the grant of all regulatory approvals necessary for the performance of thisagreement. ARTICLE XIV. FORCE MAJEURE 1. The term "force majeure" as used herein shall mean acts of God, strikes, lockouts, or other industrial disturbances; acts of the public enemy, wars, blockades, insurrections, riots, epidemics, landslides, lightning, earthquakes, fires, storms (including but not limited to tornadoes or tornado warnings), crevasses, floods, washouts; arrests and restraints of the government, either Federal or State, civil or military or civil disturbances. Relative to TGPC's and Honeoye's service and system operations, force majeure shall also mean shutdowns for purposes of necessary repairs, relocation, or construction of facilities; breakage or accident to machinery, wells or lines of pipe or casings; testing (as required by governmental authority or as deemed necessary by TGPC and/or Honeoye for the safe operation of the underground storage reservoir and facilities required to perform the service hereunder), the necessity of making repairs or alterations to machinery or lines of pipe; failure of wells, surface equipment or pipe lines, well or line freeze ups; accidents, breakdowns, inability to obtain necessary materials, or supplies or permits, or labor or land rights to perform or comply with any obligation or condition of this agreement; and any other causes, whether of the kind herein enumerated or otherwise which are not reasonably in TGPC's and/or Honeoye's control. It is understood and agreed that the settlement of strikes or lockouts or controversies with landowners involving rights of way shall be entirely within TGPC's and/or Honeoye's discretion and that the above requirement that any force majeure shall be remedied with all reasonable dispatch shall not require the settlement of strikes or lockouts or controversies with landowners involving rights of way by acceding to the demands of the opposing party when such course is inadvisable in the discretion of TGPC and/or Honeoye. 2. If by reason of force majeure either party hereto is rendered unable, wholly or in part, to carry out its obligations under this agreement, it is agreed that on such party giving notice in full particulars of such force majeure in writing to the other party within a reasonable time after the occurrence of the cause relied on, the party giving such notice, so far as and to the extent that it is affected by such force majeure, shall not be liable in damages during the continuance of any inability so caused, but for no longer period, and such cause shall so far as possible be remedied with all reasonable dispatch. ARTICLE XV. THERMAL CONVERSION 1. All volumes stated in this Rate Schedule are converted from Mcf to thermal units of MMBtu at a conversion rateas determined by TGPC.The quantities of gas that NFGDC receives from Honeoye each month will be determined by multiplying the volumes of gas received at the meter points listed in Article XI times the average BTU value reported for that month by TGPC at its interconnection point with Honeoye. ARTICLE XVI. MISCELLANEOUS 1. Upon receipt of gas, Honeoye shall be in exclusive control and possession of gas received from NFGDC until equivalent quantities of natural gas have been delivered for the account of NFGDC after which NFGDC shall be in exclusive control and possession of such gas.Honeoye shall have no responsibility for gas received from NFGDC prior to its receipt into Honeoye's system from TGPC or after its delivery to NFGDC. NFGDC shall have no responsibility for gas received from Honeoye prior to its delivery to NFGDC. 2. Each partywarrants for itself, its successors, and assigns, that it has, or will have, at the time of delivery of the natural gas, title to such gas and/or good right to cause the gas to be delivered tothe other party. Each partywarrants for itself, its successors, and assigns, that the gas it warrants hereunder shall be free and clear of all liens, encumbrances or claims, that it will indemnify and save the other partyharmless from all suits, actions, debts, accounts, damages, costs, losses, and expenses arising from or out of adverse claims of any and all persons to said gas and/or to royalties, taxes, license fees, or charges thereon which are directly applicable to such delivery of natural gas and that it will indemnify and save the other partyharmless from all taxes or assessments which may be directly levied and assessed upon such delivery and which are by law payable and the obligation of the party making such delivery. 3. No waiver by either Honeoye or NFGDC of any one or more defaults by the other in the performance of any provisions hereunder shall operate or be construed as a waiver of any future default or defaults, whether of a like or a different character. 4. It is expressly agreed that there is no third-party beneficiary to this agreement, and that the provisions of this agreement do not impart enforceable rights in anyone who is not a party or successor or assignee of any party to this agreement. 5. Neither Honeoye nor NFGDC shall in any event be liable to the other for special, incidental, consequential, penalty, or indirect damages, whether arising in contract or tort. 6. Honeoye and NFGDC acknowledge that the gas delivered by Honeoye to NFGDC is not treated or processed prior to or at the time of delivery to NFGDC. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Parties reserve all their rights, remedies and defenses with respect to any damages or concerns that arise from water vapor and/or other gas quality concerns associated with the gas delivered pursuant to this agreement. HONEOYE STORAGE CORPORATION By:Richard Norman Vice President NATIONAL FUEL GAS DISTRIBUTION CORPORATION By:Bruce Heine Vice President Exhibit 1 NFGDC/Honeoye Interconnection in Honeoye Field
